{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

  <h3>States</h3>
  <p>Accordions can be collapsed and expanded to hide or reveal information when toggled. By default, they load with all panels collapsed (this can be customized), allowing users to get a high-level overview of the content.</p>

  <h3>Collapsing and expanding</h3>
  <p>Accordion panels can be collapsed or expanded by clicking on or tapping the container where the section text label and the caret icon are positioned. When a panel is collapsed, the caret icon points to the right. When a panel expands, the caret icon rotates 90º and points down, revealing the content inside.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="multi-column--min-300-wide margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/avatar/avatar-behavior-1.png' | url }}">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h3>Multiple panels</h3>
  <p>Multiple panels can be expanded simultaneously or they can stack. Expanding one panel doesn’t collapse another which makes it easy to compare content in the same view.</p>

  {% call components.example(palette='light') %}
  <div class="multi-column--min-100-wide margin-top--1 margin-bottom--1">
    <img src="{{ '/assets/avatar/avatar-responsive-1.png' | url }}">
  </div>
  {%- endcall %}

  <h3>Tab order</h3>
  <p>When the Tab key is pressed repeatedly, the focus indicator moves from top to bottom. When a user expands a panel by pressing the Enter or Space keys, any interactive elements inside are added to the tab order before the focus indicator reaches the next panel.</p>

